                .row
                    .col-sm-12.col-md-10.col-md-offset-1
                        h3 My design process
                        h4 I work as a web developer so my design workflow differs from that of a graphic designer or illustrator. I like to design things that are outside the box as it provides a challenge to craft them into reality. This is basically how I work:
                        .row
                            .col-sm-6.col-md-3
                                h5 1. Research
                                p Design is not art - it’s a solution to a problem. It requires understanding what your users need. As Occam’s Razor states: the simplest solution is usually the correct one.
                            .col-sm-6.col-md-3
                                h5 2. Mockup
                                p Produce basic wireframes, sketches and mockups in my DotGrid book. Pen and paper is still my favourite way of jotting down an idea that needs further refinement.
                            .col-sm-6.col-md-3
                                h5 3. Share
                                p Good design doesn’t belong to you, it belongs to the world. I use Invision and Dropbox to share my ideas with others, gather feedback and keep iterating until it works.
                            .col-sm-6.col-md-3
                                h5 4. Explore
                                p Ideas are never complete as long as someone is working on them. After completing a design, I like to work on radical designs that re-imagine the core concept of the product.
